        ' Sake Shop
      p 
       ' For lunch we hit up the popular 
       a href="http://tiger-center4.com/" target="_blank" title="Center4 Hamburgers" Center4 Hamburgers
       ' . It's a burger joint that prides itself on serving great American-style burgers. I was impressed with my cheeseburger. It tasted fantastic. Vlod ordered the vegetarian burger which turned out to be a bun with burger accompaniments but no patty. He was disappointed because he was looking forward to a hot burger after freezing in the damp weather. The restaurant was really popular with young Japanese and the decor was American diner with Johnny Cash playing in the background. 
      .photo 
        .hisrc
          img src="/images/takayama/veggie_burger/veggie_burger.jpg" data-1x="/images/takayama/veggie_burger/veggie_burger-1x.jpg" data-2x="/images/takayama/veggie_burger/veggie_burger-2x.jpg" alt="Veggie Burger"
        ' Veggie Burger
      p After lunch we continued to walk around, sampling some street food, a grilled rice cake with soy sauce. 
      p 
       ' For supper we found a French cafe, 
       a href="http://www.happycow.net/reviews.php?id=6103" target="_blank" title="Cafe Flore" Cafe Flore
       ' . We arrived a little before they opened so we walked around and ended up having drinks at a local bar. The bartender was so excited to serve us. He used a translator on his phone to converse with us. We drank sake, but the bartender later told us that almost no one drinks sake in Japan. It's all beer and whiskey for them. Go figure.
      p At Cafe Flore, I had a croque monsieur and Vlod had a simple, but delicious, pasta. For dessert, we had a sweet crepe. It was a great meal and not too expensive.
